        <div2>
          <head>
            <title type="main">JOB <hi rend="i">REVIVAL</hi></title>
          </head>
          <p>This summer, the Birmingham Royal Ballet revived Dame Ninette de Valois’s <hi rend="i">Job</hi>
ballet. “<hi rend="i">Job</hi> had not been staged for 20 years. . . . <hi rend="i">Job</hi> is
distinguished in every respect. Its score by Ralph Vaughan Williams resounds with solemn beauty. . . . At the
conclusion of <hi rend="i">Job</hi> at the Royal Opera House, there was a moment of silence. It was as if a
church service had ended. But hearty applause followed. <hi rend="i">Job</hi> is decidedly worth preserving”
(<hi rend="i">The New York Times</hi>, 26 September 1993).</p>
        </div2>
